doc.previous: The first PW2000 series engine, the PW2037, powered the Boeing 757-200 and entered service with Delta Air Lines as the launch customer for the civil aviation version of the engine.
doc.after: Other than the 757, the PW2000 series engines also power the C-17 Globemaster III military transport; the United States Department of Defense designation for the engine is F117,[3][4] with the specific variant used on the C-17 being the F117-PW-100.[5] The powerplant first flew on the C-17 in 1991.
